"v.干涉，干预 【英】 v. 干涉, 干预(interfere) 【考】 officious : meddle / disaffected : rebel(多管闲事的[人]喜欢 干涉/不满的[人]喜欢 反叛) v. 干涉, 干预 【记】源于: mix(v /n 混合)把别人的事情弄得混乱－干涉源于: middle(n / adj 中间的)到了别人的中间－干涉 【参】medley(n 混杂的人群; adj 混合的) 【类】officious: meddle = disaffected: rebel多管闲事的人喜欢干涉 = 不满的人喜欢反叛meddlesome: pry = contentious: argue多管闲事的人喜欢探察 = 好争吵的人喜欢争吵attentive: meddlesome = envious: jealous特别注意的是多管闲事的 = 特别羨慕的是嫉妒的(褒贬) 【记】middle 到中间来干涉，比如两人在吵架，第三方干涉 meddle (v.)  early 14c., ""to mingle, blend, mix,"" from Old North French medler (Old French mesler, 12c., Modern French mêler) ""to mix, mingle, to meddle,"" from Vulgar Latin *misculare (source of Provençal mesclar, Spanish mezclar, Italian mescolare, meschiare), from Latin miscere ""to mix"" (see mix (v.)). From late 14c. as ""busy oneself, be concerned with, engage in;"" also disparagingly ""interfere, be officious, make a nuisance of oneself"" (the notion is of meddling too much). From mid-14c. to 1700, it also was a euphemism for ""have sexual intercourse."" Related: Meddled; meddling."
